SUBJECT--

76
00:04:56,255 --> 00:04:58,173
FORMER GOVERNOR
KODOS OF TARSUS IV,

77
00:04:58,298 --> 00:05:01,927
ALSO KNOWN AS KODOS
THE EXECUTIONER.

78
00:05:02,052 --> 00:05:06,389
AFTER THAT,
BACKGROUND ON ACTOR
ANTON KARIDIAN.

79
00:05:06,514 --> 00:05:07,849
WORKING.

80
00:05:09,726 --> 00:05:13,188
KODOS THE EXECUTIONER.
SUMMARY--

81
00:05:13,354 --> 00:05:16,650
GOVERNOR OF TARSUS IV
20 EARTH YEARS AGO.

82
00:05:16,775 --> 00:05:18,359
INVOKED MARTIAL LAW.

83
00:05:18,485 --> 00:05:20,361
SLAUGHTERED
50% OF POPULATION

84
00:05:20,487 --> 00:05:22,614
EARTH COLONY
THAT PLANET.

85
00:05:22,739 --> 00:05:25,826
BURNED BODY FOUND
WHEN EARTH FORCES ARRIVED.

86
00:05:25,951 --> 00:05:28,287
NO POSITIVE
IDENTIFICATION.

87
00:05:28,411 --> 00:05:32,082
CASE CLOSED.
DETAILED INFORMATION
FOLLOWS.

88
00:05:32,207 --> 00:05:35,919
ON STARDATE 2794.7--

89
00:05:36,044 --> 00:05:38,588
STOP.
KODOS--

90
00:05:38,713 --> 00:05:40,841
INFORMATION
ON ANTON KARIDIAN.

91
00:05:44,136 --> 00:05:45,220
DIRECTOR AND STAR

92
00:05:45,344 --> 00:05:47,264
OF TRAVELING
COMPANY OF ACTORS

93
00:05:47,388 --> 00:05:51,101
SPONSORED BY GALACTIC
CULTURAL EXCHANGE PROJECT.

94
00:05:51,226 --> 00:05:54,646
TOURING OFFICIAL
INSTALLATIONS
LAST 9 YEARS.

95
00:05:54,771 --> 00:05:57,191
HAS DAUGHTER LENORE,
19 YEARS OLD--

96
00:05:57,316 --> 00:05:59,985
STOP. GIVE COMPARATIVE
IDENTIFICATION

97
00:06:00,110 --> 00:06:02,904
BETWEEN
THE ACTOR KARIDIAN
AND GOVERNOR KODOS.

98
00:06:04,531 --> 00:06:06,783
NO IDENTIFICATION
RECORDS AVAILABLE

99
00:06:06,908 --> 00:06:09,119
ON ACTOR ANTON KARIDIAN.

100
00:06:12,622 --> 00:06:15,125
GIVE INFORMATION
ON ACTOR KARIDIAN

101
00:06:15,250 --> 00:06:16,710
PRIOR TO KODOS'S DEATH.

102
00:06:19,713 --> 00:06:22,132
NO INFORMATION
AVAILABLE
ANTON KARIDIAN

103
00:06:22,257 --> 00:06:24,176
PRIOR TO
20 YEARS AGO.

104
00:06:29,556 --> 00:06:30,849
PHOTOGRAPH KODOS.

105
00:06:35,229 --> 00:06:36,604
PHOTOGRAPH KARIDIAN.

106
00:06:41,902 --> 00:06:43,486
NOW PHOTOGRAPH BOTH.

107
00:06:50,911 --> 00:06:51,661
MR. SPOCK.

108
00:06:53,538 --> 00:06:55,414
YOU KNOW DR. LEIGHTON,
DON'T YOU?

109
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:59,169
WOULD YOU SAY
HE'S GIVEN TO FANTASY?

110
00:06:59,294 --> 00:07:01,504
A GOOD EMPIRICAL
RESEARCH SCIENTIST.

111
00:07:01,629 --> 00:07:03,673
STEADY, REPUTABLE,
OCCASIONALLY BRILLIANT.

112
00:07:03,798 --> 00:07:05,884
WITH A VERY LONG MEMORY.

113
00:07:06,009 --> 00:07:08,053
I HAVE
NO INFORMATION
ON THAT, CAPTAIN.

114
00:07:08,178 --> 00:07:09,679
WE ARE READY
TO LEAVE ORBIT.

115
00:07:09,804 --> 00:07:12,599
WE'LL DELAY DEPARTURE
FOR A TIME.

116
00:07:12,724 --> 00:07:14,768
I'M BEAMING BACK DOWN
TO THE PLANET AGAIN.

117
00:07:17,562 --> 00:07:19,856
[LAUGHTER]

118
00:07:24,861 --> 00:07:26,196
WHERE'S TOM?

119
00:07:26,321 --> 00:07:27,364
HE WENT TO TOWN.

120
00:07:27,488 --> 00:07:29,991
HE CALLED.
HE'S ON HIS WAY BACK.

121
00:07:47,217 --> 00:07:49,428
THE OTHERS
ARE ON THE PATIO.

122
00:07:49,552 --> 00:07:52,722
I TAKE IT YOU'RE
THE WELCOMING COMMITTEE.

123
00:07:52,847 --> 00:07:54,308
IS THAT FOR ME?

124
00:07:54,433 --> 00:07:55,767
WHY NOT?

125
00:07:58,478 --> 00:08:00,897
I SAW YOUR
PERFORMANCE TONIGHT.

126
00:08:01,022 --> 00:08:02,649
MAY I EXTEND
MY APPRECIATION?

127
00:08:02,774 --> 00:08:04,776
MY FATHER WILL BE
DELIGHTED, MR...

128
00:08:04,901 --> 00:08:05,777
MR...

129
00:08:05,902 --> 00:08:07,112
CAPTAIN JAMES KIRK,

130
00:08:07,237 --> 00:08:08,863
STARSHIP "ENTERPRISE."

131
00:08:08,989 --> 00:08:10,573
OH. WE'RE HONORED.

132
00:08:12,617 --> 00:08:13,994
I HAD HOPED
TO MEET YOUR FATHER

133
00:08:14,119 --> 00:08:15,203
HERE TONIGHT PERSONALLY.

134
00:08:15,329 --> 00:08:17,247
I'M SORRY,
CAPTAIN KIRK.

135
00:08:17,372 --> 00:08:19,791
HE HAS A RIGID RULE
ABOUT THAT.

136
00:08:19,916 --> 00:08:21,668
HE NEVER SEES ANYONE
PERSONALLY,

137
00:08:21,793 --> 00:08:23,003
AND HE NEVER
ATTENDS PARTIES.

138
00:08:23,128 --> 00:08:24,963
AN ACTOR TURNING AWAY
HIS ADMIRERS?

139
00:08:25,088 --> 00:08:26,714
VERY UNUSUAL.

140
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:29,426
KARIDIAN IS A MOST
UNUSUAL MAN.

141
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:31,511
YOU SAW "MACBETH."

142
00:08:31,636 --> 00:08:32,720
THAT WAS MY FATHER.

143
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:37,267
WELL, THEN I'LL TALK
TO LADY MACBETH.

144
00:08:40,812 --> 00:08:43,523
SO, CAPTAIN
OF THE "ENTERPRISE."

145
00:08:43,648 --> 00:08:44,732
INTERESTING.

146
00:08:44,858 --> 00:08:48,153
SO, LADY MACBETH.
INTERESTING.

147
00:08:48,278 --> 00:08:49,529
WHAT'S YOUR NEXT MOVE?

148
00:08:53,574 --> 00:08:57,245
WE PLAY TWO PERFORMANCES
AT BENECIA

149
00:08:57,371 --> 00:08:58,997
IF THE "ASTRAL QUEEN"
CAN GET US THERE.

150
00:08:59,122 --> 00:09:00,874
SHE'S A GOOD SHIP.

151
00:09:02,501 --> 00:09:03,584
THANK YOU.

152
00:09:03,710 --> 00:09:05,837
YOU WERE VERY IMPRESSIVE
AS LADY MACBETH.

153
00:09:05,962 --> 00:09:07,672
THANK YOU.

154
00:09:09,508 --> 00:09:10,633
AND AS LENORE KARIDIAN?

155
00:09:13,261 --> 00:09:14,554
VERY IMPRESSIVE.

156
00:09:17,182 --> 00:09:18,266
LENORE.

157
00:09:21,811 --> 00:09:23,146
I'D LIKE
TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

158
00:09:23,271 --> 00:09:25,399
YOU MEAN PROFESSIONALLY?

159
00:09:25,524 --> 00:09:26,774
NOT NECESSARILY.

160
00:09:28,609 --> 00:09:31,446
I THINK I'D LIKE THAT.

161
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:34,824
UNFORTUNATELY,
WE MUST KEEP A SCHEDULE.

162
00:09:34,949 --> 00:09:37,452
YOU DON'T HAVE A SCHEDULE
NOW, DO YOU?

163
00:09:37,577 --> 00:09:39,496
YOU MEAN LEAVE?

164
00:09:39,620 --> 00:09:40,830
BUT I'VE ONLY
JUST ARRIVED.

165
00:09:40,955 --> 00:09:42,665
SO HAVE I.

166
00:09:42,790 --> 00:09:43,708
AND YOU HATE
TO OVERSTAY
A WELCOME.

167
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:46,253
EXACTLY.

168
00:09:46,378 --> 00:09:47,546
WHY NOT?

169
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:49,756
GOOD.

170
00:09:49,881 --> 00:09:52,133
I'LL MAKE OUR APOLOGIES
TO OUR HOSTESS.

171
00:09:52,259 --> 00:09:53,676
I'LL MEET YOU OUTSIDE.

172
00:10:05,688 --> 00:10:07,065
TIRED OF WALKING?

173
00:10:07,190 --> 00:10:09,568
NO. JUST THINKING.

174
00:10:09,692 --> 00:10:11,528
ABOUT WHAT?

175
00:10:11,652 --> 00:10:14,781
AT THE PARTY, YOU WERE
SUCH A BRASH YOUNG MAN.

176
00:10:14,906 --> 00:10:16,032
AND NOW?

177
00:10:16,157 --> 00:10:17,700
NOW SOMEHOW DIFFERENT.

178
00:10:17,825 --> 00:10:19,578
NOT A SHIP'S CAPTAIN
WITH ALL THOSE PEOPLE

179
00:10:19,702 --> 00:10:23,331
TO BE STRONG
AND CONFIDENT
IN FRONT OF.

180
00:10:23,457 --> 00:10:26,960
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE
REALLY VERY DEAR,
AREN'T YOU?

181
00:10:27,085 --> 00:10:28,628
IN SOME WAYS...

182
00:10:30,338 --> 00:10:31,465
VERY LONELY.

183
00:10:49,441 --> 00:10:50,858
IT'S TOM LEIGHTON.

184
00:10:53,736 --> 00:10:54,613
HE'S DEAD.

185
00:11:01,953 --> 00:11:04,539
TOM...

186
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:09,419
AT LEAST
HE HAS PEACE NOW.

187
00:11:09,544 --> 00:11:11,505
HE NEVER REALLY
HAD THAT BEFORE.

188
00:11:13,881 --> 00:11:16,217
OH,
WHY WAS TOM KILLED

189
00:11:16,343 --> 00:11:18,011
IF WHAT HE SUSPECTED
WASN'T TRUE?

190
00:11:18,136 --> 00:11:19,137
I DON'T KNOW.

191
00:11:19,262 --> 00:11:21,014
I'LL TRY AND FIND OUT.

192
00:11:22,807 --> 00:11:24,892
OH, JIM.

193
00:11:25,018 --> 00:11:26,811
HOW I'LL MISS HIM.

194
00:11:38,657 --> 00:11:40,283
KIRK TO "ENTERPRISE."

195
00:11:40,408 --> 00:11:41,451
Uhura: BRIDGE
HERE, CAPTAIN.

196
00:11:41,576 --> 00:11:44,120
PUT ME THROUGH
TO CAPTAIN JOHN DALEY

197
00:11:44,245 --> 00:11:46,289
OF THE "ASTRAL QUEEN"
IN ORBIT STATION,

198
00:11:46,414 --> 00:11:48,958
AND PUT IT ON SCRAMBLE,
WILL YOU?

199
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:50,793
CAPTAIN DALEY'S
ON, SIR.

200
00:11:50,918 --> 00:11:53,129
JOHN. JIM KIRK.

201
00:11:53,254 --> 00:11:54,964
Daley: HI, JIM.

202
00:11:55,089 --> 00:11:56,174
CAN YOU DO ME A FAVOR?

203
00:11:56,299 --> 00:11:58,926
I OWE YOU A DOZEN.
JUST ASK.

204
00:11:59,052 --> 00:12:00,761
DON'T MAKE
YOUR PICKUP HERE.

205
00:12:00,887 --> 00:12:02,847
YOU MEAN STRAND
ALL THOSE ACTORS?

206
00:12:02,972 --> 00:12:04,516
I'LL PICK THEM UP.

207
00:12:04,641 --> 00:12:05,517
AND IF THERE'S
ANY TROUBLE,

208
00:12:05,642 --> 00:12:07,227
IT'LL BE
MY RESPONSIBILITY.

209
00:12:07,352 --> 00:12:09,062
WILL DO.
ANYTHING ELSE?

210
00:12:10,647 --> 00:12:12,691
JUST KEEP THIS
BETWEEN THE TWO OF US

211
00:12:12,815 --> 00:12:15,151
AND ACCEPT MY THANKS.
OVER AND OUT.

212
00:12:15,276 --> 00:12:16,361
KIRK TO "ENTERPRISE."

213
00:12:16,486 --> 00:12:18,071
Uhura: BRIDGE
HERE, CAPTAIN.

214
00:12:18,196 --> 00:12:19,406
TRANSPORTER ROOM.

215
00:12:19,531 --> 00:12:20,615
READY TO BEAM UP.

216
00:12:31,626 --> 00:12:32,960
AHA.

217
00:12:36,631 --> 00:12:39,133
READY TO RESUME
COURSE, CAPTAIN.

218
00:12:39,259 --> 00:12:41,844
I THINK WE'RE DUE
FOR A PICKUP.

219
00:12:42,761 --> 00:12:45,890
WHAT KIND,
PERSONNEL? CARGO?

220
00:12:46,015 --> 00:12:47,350
CAPTAIN?

221
00:12:47,475 --> 00:12:50,019
A MISS KARIDIAN HAS BEEN
TRANSPORTED ABOARD SHIP.

222
00:12:50,144 --> 00:12:51,979
SHE REQUESTS PERMISSION
TO SEE YOU.

223
00:12:52,105 --> 00:12:55,275
TELL HER TO COME
UP TO THE BRIDGE.

224
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:57,444
Uhura: ESCORT MISS KARIDIAN
TO THE BRIDGE.

225
00:13:07,912 --> 00:13:10,624
HOW DID YOU KNOW
THIS LADY
WAS COMING ABOARD?

226
00:13:10,749 --> 00:13:12,083
I'M THE CAPTAIN.

227
00:13:20,007 --> 00:13:22,594
CAPTAIN KIRK,
I DIDN'T THINK WE'D BE
MEETING AGAIN SO SOON.

228
00:13:22,719 --> 00:13:23,678
YOU PROBABLY
WOULDN'T BELIEVE ME

229
00:13:23,802 --> 00:13:25,054
IF I TOLD YOU
I ARRANGED IT.

230
00:13:25,179 --> 00:13:28,224
NO, BUT IT'S
A DELIGHTFUL THOUGHT.

231
00:13:28,349 --> 00:13:30,101
CAPTAIN, I'M AFRAID
WE NEED YOUR HELP.

232
00:13:30,226 --> 00:13:32,312
WE'VE BEEN STRANDED.

233
00:13:32,437 --> 00:13:33,772
IT SEEMS
THAT OUR TRANSPORTATION

234
00:13:33,896 --> 00:13:35,398
HAS CANCELED OUT
ON US.

235
00:13:35,523 --> 00:13:37,275
CAN'T YOU MAKE
OTHER ARRANGEMENTS?

236
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:38,526
WELL, YES,
BUT NOT IN TIME.

237
00:13:38,652 --> 00:13:41,237
YOU SEE, OUR SCHEDULE
IS LIKE A CHAIN.

238
00:13:41,362 --> 00:13:43,448
ONE BREAK
AND IT ALL COLLAPSES.

239
00:13:43,573 --> 00:13:44,991
BE A SHAME
IF THAT HAPPENED.

240
00:13:46,660 --> 00:13:48,703
IF EVER WE NEEDED
A GOOD SAMARITAN.

241
00:13:52,999 --> 00:13:54,959
WELL, I...

242
00:13:55,084 --> 00:13:56,377
I APPEAL TO YOU.

